---
description: Use RTK (Rust Token Killer) for Shell commands to reduce token usage
alwaysApply: true
---

# RTK Shell Commands

RTK hook may not intercept Agent Shell automatically. **Always prefix** dev commands with `rtk` when using the Shell tool.

## Rules

- `git status` → `rtk git status` (never bare `git status`)
- `npm run build` → `rtk npm run build`
- `mvn ...` → `rtk mvn ...`
- `flutter test` → `rtk test flutter test` or `rtk err flutter test`
- Do **NOT** double-prefix: `rtk rtk git status` is wrong
- Skip `rtk` for: `cd`, `mkdir`, `echo`, pure path navigation

## Quick reference

| Instead of | Use |
|------------|-----|
| `git status` | `rtk git status` |
| `git diff --stat` | `rtk git diff --stat` |
| `git log -n 10` | `rtk git log -n 10` |
| `npm run build` | `rtk npm run build` |
| `mvn clean install` | `rtk mvn clean install` |
| `cat file` / read via shell | `rtk read file` |
| `grep pattern .` | `rtk grep "pattern" .` |
| `find ...` | `rtk find "..." .` |
| test runners | `rtk test <cmd>` or `rtk jest` / `rtk vitest` / `rtk pytest` |
| lint / tsc | `rtk lint` / `rtk tsc` |
| errors only | `rtk err <cmd>` |

## Files & search

```
rtk ls .
rtk read path/to/file
rtk read path/to/file -l aggressive   # signatures only
rtk smart path/to/file                # 2-line summary
rtk find "*.ts" .
rtk grep "pattern" .
rtk diff file1 file2
```

## Git (compact output)

```
rtk git status
rtk git log -n 10
rtk git diff
rtk git add .
rtk git commit -m "msg"
rtk git push
rtk git pull
```

## Analytics

```
rtk gain
rtk gain --history
```

Built-in Read/Grep/Glob tools bypass RTK hook — prefer Shell + `rtk read` / `rtk grep` when output is large.
